<p>The Button component provides a consistent interface for interactive elements with multiple variants and sizes.</p>

<h3>When to Use</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Primary actions in forms and interfaces</li>
  <li>Navigation and interaction triggers</li>
  <li>Call-to-action elements</li>
</ul>

<h3>Variants Guide</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Primary:</strong> Main actions (save, submit, continue)</li>
  <li><strong>Secondary:</strong> Secondary actions (cancel, back)</li>
  <li><strong>Danger:</strong> Destructive actions (delete, remove)</li>
  <li><strong>Link:</strong> Text-only buttons that look like links</li>
</ul>

<h3>Accessibility</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Always provide meaningful text or aria-label</li>
  <li>Use appropriate button types (submit for forms)</li>
  <li>Consider focus states for keyboard navigation</li>
</ul>